-{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T17:07:53.456Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777309673456_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-011@20260427t001208z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-011@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-27\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `docs/runbooks/generation-backend.md`\n- `tests/test_runbook_generation_backend.py`\n- `specs/t-011@20260427t001208z-spec.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe runbook accurately reflects the current state of the generation backend as described in the specification. It provides correct commands for checking budget state, queue status, and performing operations like backend switching and IDyOM LTM rollback.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria are met:\n- Covers status checks, budget cap adjustments, backend switching (Replicate/Modal/local), IDyOM LTM rollback, queue clearance, cache inspection, and disk locations.\n- Documents all relevant environment variables (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD`, etc.) with their default values.\n- Includes 5 distinct worked-example debugging scenarios.\n- Cross-links to `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` and `idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example`.\n\n## Consistency\nThe runbook follows the established style of `docs/r750-bare-metal-runbook.md`, using H1 titles, part-style H2 sections, tables for configurations, and bash blocks for commands. It consistently uses UTC for dated directories and rollovers as requested.\n\n## Security\nNo secrets or API keys are included in the documentation. Placeholders and environment variable names are used correctly.\n\n## Quality\nThe documentation is clear, well-structured, and includes a static regression test (`tests/test_runbook_generation_backend.py`) to prevent future drift.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None. (The `PermissionError` encountered during the full test suite `pytest tests/ -x` is a pre-existing environment/seatbelt issue unrelated to this documentation task).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nWork is excellent. The static regression test provides strong assurance against future documentation drift.\n"}}
