5:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.
7:- Added the CypherClaw narrative beat endpoint (T-011@20260502T001347Z): `POST /beats/next` now validates `{cycle_number, domain_filter, arc_position_target?, force_arc_event?}`, wraps an injected or lazily imported deploy-side `NarrativeEngine.next_beat()`, preserves the engine-owned serialized `StoryBeat` JSON shape without padding absent fields, and returns clear `503` unavailable / `502` generation-failure errors. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_beats.py` pins parameter passing, raw mapping shape preservation, dataclass/nested serialization, validation-before-engine behavior, downstream failure handling, missing-engine fallback, and shared-secret auth behavior.
9:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
